    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped basil </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 3 min until it resembles a thick bolognese sauce consistency – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat it<strong> </strong>dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper (squeeze as much liquid out as you can!) then tear into chunks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
